Photos show recently born polar bear cub, Brodie, exploring its enclosure at the Highland Wildlife Park in Edinburgh, Scotland in the UK for the first time. The public viewing of Brodie and mum Victoria will be open on March 28, but they will only be shown for short period of time to begin with, according to the park staff. (All photos via VCG) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)